{
  "stem": "6159.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that-- I could only go out if I could shift myself between the crowd, and I must have been very lucky or very agile to do that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Not-- not even my papers were asked.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was just pushing myself out with the crowd, and I was rushing onto the first train, but was stopped there and I was getting on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, I couldn't run because I didn't want to make a spectacle out of myself.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was just going steady and get on the first train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I went for a few stops and get off, and I went to the proper train that took me to this address where my sister was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, when she saw me and opened the door, she was-- we were crying both terribly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was just a lucky escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think everybody who came out of this Holocaust is a lucky person.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the man the you married had provided you the papers and your sister the papers?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He-- he found her the place as well, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, we-- we survived there, but they were bombing all the time, and we had to go down to the-- the celery.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Cellar?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Cellar.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sorry.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And because there were a lot of non-Jewish people as well in the building still, you know the-- the boy was-- her boy was about, oh, how old was-- was-- he?",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was born in '40, just one second, '41. 1941, so he was just a two or three years old boy, and when he had to go to-- to do some [INAUDIBLE], we surrounded, you know, a few people who know the story, we surrounded him like it would be a game, so not to see that he is a Jewish boy.",
      "word_count": 62
    }
  ],
